Cell.Text: [S] G|You made it! | We need to get inside. Follow me!
[S] G|Come on! We need to get inside before that dragon comes back!
G|Leave me to my work. Unless you plan to stay and help?
G|I think we're almost out. Come on!
GS|Let's take our time. I think we can sneak by her if we're careful.
GS|[E] We must be near the entrance for that bear to have made its den here.
G|I'll follow your lead.
G|Easy does it.
G|Not now.
GS|I hate those things. Too many eyes or something.
GS|Looks like we're on our own now.
GS|Since nobody's trying to kill me just now, maybe we should rest for a minute.
G|Let's see if we can find a way out of here.
G|We'd better stick together down here.
GS|I'm glad to be out of that place. I hope this leads somewhere.
GS|These bastards call themselves Imperial Legionnaires...
G|Come on. Sounds like trouble.
G|Look around. Grab anything that looks useful.
G|There may be a way out, down this way.
G|I guess that'll teach me to try to reason with a Stormcloak.
G|Let's see where this goes. We can't be the only survivors.
G|Find yourself a weapon. You're going to need it.
GS|We'd better get out of here. I don't think this place is going to stand up to much more of this.
G|Don't worry. We'll get out of here, somehow.
G|I can't decide if things are about to get worse or better.
G|At least we don't have a dragon to worry about, for the moment.
G|I think we're almost out. Come on!
GS|Take it slow and careful, and I think we can sneak by her.
GS|[E] We must be near the entrance for that bear to make its den here.
G|I'll follow your lead.
G|I've got your back, don't worry.
G|Not now.
GS|Biggest damn spiders I've ever seen.
GS|The others'll have to find another way out.
GS|This is the longest day I can remember.
G|Let's see if we can find a way out of here.
G|We'd better stick together down here.
GS|I sure hope there's a way out somewhere down here.
GS|Here's the noble Empire in all its glory. Pah.
G|Come on!
G|Look around. Grab anything useful.
G|There may be a way out, down this way.
G|We'd better get moving before any more Imperials show up.
G|Let's see where this goes. Better than going back outside with that dragon.
G|Get yourself a weapon. I'm going to need your help if we run into any more Imperials.
GS|We've got to find a way out of here.
G|Don't worry. We'll get out of here, somehow.
G|I don't think this day is ever going to end.
G|Better in here than out there.
GS|Help us and you may earn a pardon.
GS|Hey, weren't you on the carts with the Stormcloaks? | Ah, well, if Hadvar vouches for you I guess it must be all right.
GS|I saw Caius.. that dragon just grabbed him and... I don't know how I made it out of there...
G|Nothing for it but to keep moving.
G|Better down here than out there.
G|A dragon.... First in a thousand years....
G|We need to find a way out of here.
G|What?
G|Worry about yourself.
GS|Thank Talos you came along... I thought I was going to die down here.
GS|Imperial dogs... there's nothing that's too low for them.
GS|You were with us on the carts, weren't you? Not your lucky day, eh?
GS|I wonder if there's any more Imperials hiding down here somewhere.
GS|Ralof seems to like you. That's good enough for me.
GS|What do you make of it... the dragon? What does it mean?
G|What next?
G|I hope someone knows where we're going.
G|Better down here than out there.
G|Just keep putting one foot in front of the other.
<<Shared>> So that's why you were in the cart. Thieving.
